Data origin

This ps object was cleaned up in Box/Kate/MrOS/data/Analyses/MrOS_EDA.Rmd. ALl of the data is described explicitly in that RMD. The ps object is rarefied

Things I want to answer: 1. How many people are dialister/mobiluncus present in? 2. What is the relative abundance only for the people that have it. 3. And what directions the associations are in

visualization tests

lollipop
#Healthy weight: 13/104 --> 12.5%
#Overweight: 53/253 --> 20.9%
#Obesity: 44/118 --> 37.3%

melt_ps$BMI_group <- factor(melt_ps$BMI_group, levels = c("healthy_weight", "overweight", "obesity"))

melt_ps$BMI_title <- "overweight"
melt_ps$BMI_title[melt_ps$BMI_group == "healthy_weight"] <- "healthy \nweight"
melt_ps$BMI_title[melt_ps$BMI_group == "obesity"] <- "obese"
melt_ps$BMI_title <- factor(melt_ps$BMI_title, levels = c("obese", "overweight", "healthy \nweight"))

y_title <- expression(paste("Proportion of samples containing ", italic("Dialister")))

# plot
BMI_lolli <- melt_ps %>%
  filter(Genus == "Dialister") %>% 
  group_by(BMI_title) %>% 
  count(Abundance > 0) %>% 
  mutate(percent_n = (n/sum(n))*100) %>% 
  filter(n < 70) %>% 
  ggplot(., aes(x=BMI_title, y= percent_n )) +
    geom_segment( aes(x=BMI_title ,xend=BMI_title, y=0, yend=percent_n), color="black") +
    geom_point(size=3, color="#69b3a2") +
  theme_bw() +
  coord_flip() +
  ylab(y_title) + xlab("")
tree map
# Plot
melt_ps %>%
  filter(Genus == "Dialister") %>% 
  group_by(BMI_group) %>% 
  count(Abundance > 0) %>%

            title="",
            palette="Dark2",

            # Borders:
            border.col=c("black"),
